stylometry: Excel does not like solivng "if" functions. Solver interger programing usualy starts off with 5 percent which will sometimes not give the optimal result. So we then have to change the 5 percent to 0 percent to get the best solution. Also if there are alot of changing cells it makes the problem that more complex and hard. The algorithim uses a branch and bound method which it chooses a given branch and follows it all the way down until there is a problem and then cuts that branch off and chooses a different branch until it finds the optimal solution.
